---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
// NOTE: baseline policy aligned with the HLB Ireland and FutureRange policies —
// have it reviewed by the group's legal adviser before launch.
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Mentora Group"
  description="How Mentora Group collects, uses and protects personal data on this website, and the rights you have under the GDPR."
>
  <section class="page-hero on-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="lede">Last updated: July 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Mentora Group ("we", "us") is the holding company of HLB Ireland and
          FutureRange. This policy explains what personal data we collect
          through this website, why we collect it, and the rights you have
          over it under the General Data Protection Regulation (EU 2016/679)
          and the Irish Data Protection Act 2018.
        </p>
        <p>
          This policy covers this website only. Personal data processed by the
          group's firms in the course of providing their services — for
          example client engagement, payroll, audit or IT service data — is
          governed by each firm's own privacy policy:
          the <a href="https://www.hlb.ie/privacy-policy/" rel="noopener">HLB Ireland privacy policy</a> and
          the <a href="https://futurerange.ie/privacy-policy-2/" rel="noopener">FutureRange privacy policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>Who is responsible for your data</h2>
        <p>
          The data controller for this website is Mentora Group, The
          Courtyard, Carmanhall Road, Sandyford, Dublin 18, D18 NW62. For any
          privacy question or request, contact
          <a href="mailto:info@hlb.ie">info@hlb.ie</a> or phone
          +353 (0)1 291 5265.
        </p>

        <h2>What we collect</h2>
        <p>
          When you contact us through this website — by form, email or phone —
          we receive the details you choose to share: your name, email
          address, company, and the content of your message.
        </p>
        <p>
          Like most websites, our hosting provider also records limited
          technical data in server logs, such as IP address, browser type and
          the date and time of visits. This website does not use advertising
          or tracking cookies.
        </p>

        <h2>Why we use it</h2>
        <p>
          We use your contact details to respond to your enquiry and to follow
          up on it — our legitimate interest in dealing with the people who
          contact us. Where the law requires us to hold or disclose
          information (for example anti-money laundering obligations that
          apply to the group's regulated services), we process it to comply
          with those legal obligations. Where we rely on your consent, you may
          withdraw it at any time.
        </p>

        <h2>Who we share it with</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell personal data. It may be shared within the Mentora
          Group companies (HLB Ireland and FutureRange) so the right team can
          answer you, and with the IT providers who host our systems, with
          professional advisers, and with regulators or authorities where the
          law requires it. Providers who process data for us do so under
          GDPR-compliant agreements.
        </p>

        <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
        <p>
          We keep personal data no longer than necessary. Enquiry
          correspondence is retained only as long as needed to handle your
          enquiry and any business relationship that follows from it. Records
          connected to the firms' regulated services are retained for the
          statutory periods set out in their own policies.
        </p>

        <h2>How we protect it</h2>
        <p>
          We apply appropriate technical and organisational measures,
          including encryption and access controls. If a personal data breach
          occurs that we are required to notify, we will notify the Data
          Protection Commission within 72 hours and, where there is a high
          risk to you, we will tell you directly.
        </p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of the
          personal data we hold about you; ask us to restrict processing or
          object to it; request a portable copy; and withdraw any consent you
          have given — all at any time, using the contact details above.
        </p>
        <p>
          You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the supervisory
          authority: the Data Protection Commission, 6 Pembroke Row, Dublin 2
          — phone +353 1 765 0100 —
          <a href="https://www.dataprotection.ie" rel="noopener">dataprotection.ie</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal { padding: 80px 0 110px; }
</style>
